1–about 1256","1171–1256":"1171–1256","1175–1222":"1175–1222","1180–Male":"1180–Deceased","1185–1210":"1185–1210","1205–Male":"1205–Deceased","1215–1247":"1215–1247","1145–1256":"1145–1256","1149–1184":"1149–1184","about 1171":"about 1171","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1149":"1149","1247":"1247","1224":"1224","1256":"1256","1145":"1145","1222":"1222","about 1205":"about 1205","1210":"1210","about 1256":"about 1256","about 1210":"about 1210","Tong Castle, Kent, England":"Tong Castle, Kent, England","Tong Castle, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tong Castle, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Badlesmere, Kent, England":"Badlesmere, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bartholomew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of New Testament origin, the name of an apostle mentioned in all the synoptic gospels (Matthew, Mark, and Luke) and in the Acts of the Apostles. It is an Aramaic formation meaning ‘son of Talmai’, and has been assumed by many scholars to be a byname of the apostle   Nathaniel .  <i>Talmai</i> is a Hebrew name, said to mean ‘abounding in furrows’ (Numbers 13:22)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Dev ."],"variants":[{"name":"Deborah","meanings":["Biblical name (meaning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":44,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":53,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Bartholomew de Badlesmere III was born about 1171, in Tong Castle, Kent, England, his father, Bartholomew de Badlesmere, was 27 and his mother, Margaret FitzGilbert de Clare, was 23. He had at least 2 sons with Margaret de Clare. He died about 1256, in his hometown, at the age of 87."},"et":{"about 1171–about 1256":"umbes 1171–umbes 1256","1171–1256":"1171–1256","1175–1222":"1175–1222","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1185–1210":"1185–1210","1205–Male":"1205–Surnud","1215–1247":"1215–1247","1145–1256":"1145–1256","1149–1184":"1149–1184","about 1171":"umbes 1171","1175":"1175","1185":"1185","1184":"1184","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1149":"1149","1247":"1247","1224":"1224","1256":"1256","1145":"1145","1222":"1222","about 1205":"umbes 1205","1210":"1210","about 1256":"umbes 1256","about 1210":"umbes 1210","Tong Castle, Kent, England":"Tong Castle, Kent, England","Tong Castle, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Tong Castle, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Badlesmere, Kent, England":"Badlesmere, Kent, England"},"fi":{"about 1171–about 1256":"noin 1171–noin 1256","1171–1256":"1171–1256